gamazons
------------------------------------------
Amazons is a game played on a 10x10 chess board. Each side has four
pieces (amazons) that move like chess queens (in a straight line in any
direction). Instead of capturing pieces like in chess, the game is
determined based on who moves last.

Each move consists of two parts. First an amazon moves to a new square
and then fires an arrow to another square (the arrow is fired in a
straight line in any direction from the square the amazon landed on).
The square the arrow lands on becomes a permenant block for the rest of
the game. No one can move over it, or fire an arrow over it. Every turn
an amazon must move and fire an arrow, so every turn there is one less
square available on the board. Try and block in your opponent or section
off a good chunk of the board for yourself. 

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.25-15
  libatk1.0_0-1.24.0-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0_0-2.14.7-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.18.4-1
  libgnome2_0-2.24.1-1
  libgnomecanvas2_0-2.20.1.1-2
  libgnomeui2_0-2.24.0-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.14.7-1
  libintl8-0.17-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf2.5-2.63-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-3
  binutils-20080624-2
  cygport-0.4.3-1
  gawk-3.1.6-1
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gnome-common-2.24.0-1
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.23a-2
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://www.yorgalily.org/gamazons/

Canonical download:
  http://www.yorgalily.org/gamazons/src/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gamazons-0.83-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./gamazons-0.83-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gamazons-0.83-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gamazons-0.83-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

